<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ladwenya</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Where shall I hunt?  I have bind, so just about any place is good now.  :-)))))<BR>I've tried in Oasis, and that's okay when I can find a group.  I'd like to find someplace where there is a higher demand for nukers, but I have no idea where.  The furthest I've been is Highhold.<P>Ladwenya<BR>Saryn<BR>High Elf<BR>Wizard</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Saell</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">At that level you can probably solo in Crushbone.  This will help develop your melee skills, so finding a group is preferable, but not necessary.  The loot is pretty good.  CB belts and lego pads give good experience when you take them to Kaladim.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dumathoin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Ladwenya:<BR><B>Where shall I hunt?  I have bind, so just about any place is good now.  :-)))))<BR>I've tried in Oasis, and that's okay when I can find a group.  I'd like to find someplace where there is a higher demand for nukers, but I have no idea where.  The furthest I've been is Highhold.<P>Ladwenya<BR>Saryn<BR>High Elf<BR>Wizard</B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>You can nuke, you have a pet. You can solo Crushbone but I would suggest hiring at least 1 dumb warrior tank to accompany you just in case Orcs surround you. Offer to split the CB belts with him. Forget the cents. Get the Legionnaires. <P>Northern Desert of Ro or Oasis is good for your level. Tons of blues to yellows at your level. Most creatures wont gang up on you in the desert. <P>West Commons! At level 14, the majority of west commons critters were still blue to my beefy Paladin. Go on a Kodiak bear hunt all day! Pick off wisps, loot the Greater Lightstones. Kill bandits - good if you're with a group. </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Relevancy</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">To be honest your best bet is to try and find other people who play when you do and get in with them.  As My wizard hit lvl 9 plus I amost always grouped with the same people.  It is hard as a wizard to solo, without a ton of down time, but if  you find a tank to hang with it helps tremendously.  As long as you know that your job is to "finish" them.  Not to bring them down completely!<P>Good luck to you where ever you decide to go<P>From a Retired wizard<BR></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
